data.current_description: Runs a pipeline. The returned Operation's metadata field will contain a google.cloud.lifesciences.v2beta.Metadata object describing the status of the pipeline execution. The response field will contain a google.cloud.lifesciences.v2beta.RunPipelineResponse object if the pipeline completes successfully. **Note:** Before you can use this method, the *Life Sciences Service Agent* must have access to your project. This is done automatically when the Cloud Life Sciences API is first enabled, but if you delete this permission you must disable and re-enable the API to grant the Life Sciences Service Agent the required permissions. Authorization requires the following [Google IAM](https://cloud.google.com/iam/) permission: * `lifesciences.workflows.run`
data.description_suggestion: Executes a pipeline workflow asynchronously. Accepts a RunPipelineRequest containing the pipeline specification, environment, and execution parameters. Returns a long-running Operation whose metadata contains execution status and whose response contains RunPipelineResponse upon successful completion. The Life Sciences Service Agent must have project access (automatically granted when API is enabled). Authorization requires the `lifesciences.workflows.run` IAM permission.
data.reasoning: Missing summary. Description is verbose and unclear about input requirements (RunPipelineRequest).
